- modify, adapt, translate, or create derivative works of QQueue Cloud;
- reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise attempt to derive
  source code, underlying ideas, algorithms, or implementation details;
- remove, alter, or obscure copyright, license, trademark, or proprietary
  notices;
- bypass, disable, or interfere with license checks, usage limits, metering, or
  access restrictions;
- use QQueue Cloud to offer a competing hosted service or managed service to
  third parties.

4. Payment, Expiration, and Termination

If payment stops, a subscription expires, or the customer's commercial or
self-hosted license terminates, this license terminates automatically.

When this license terminates:

- the customer must stop using QQueue Cloud unless the customer renews or
  receives written permission from Nana Aboagye Boateng;
- access to updates and support ends;
- the customer must delete or stop using proprietary QQueue Cloud code except as
  otherwise required by law or explicitly allowed in writing.

